"{\"uid\": \"independent.co.uk-sport-olympics-paris-olympics-river-seine-sewage-mayor-b2581116.html\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"Notifications can be managed in browser preferences.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 52, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Please refresh the page or navigate to another page on the site to be automatically logged inPlease refresh your browser to be logged in  Swipe for next article  Removed from bookmarks  I would like to be emailed about offers, events and updates from The Independent.\", \"from\": 54, \"to\": 321, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Read ourPrivacy notice  Watch asParismayorAnne Hidalgoswam in the River Seine on Wednesday, 17 July, as the city prepares to host the 2024Olympics.\", \"from\": 322, \"to\": 469, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 388, \"end\": 399, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"River Seine\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Organisers have invested \\u20ac1.4bn ($1.5bn) toimprove the cleanlinessof the Seine for the Games and to ensure Parisians have a cleaner river in the years after it finishes.\", \"from\": 471, \"to\": 640, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"However, a few spells of heavy rain could push E. coli levels beyond the limit of 900 colony-forming units per 100ml that the World Triathlon Federation has determined as safe for competitions.\", \"from\": 642, \"to\": 835, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 768, \"end\": 783, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Triathlon\", \"score\": 0.9999995621511565, \"rank\": 4.3784906452659505e-07, \"text\": \"World Triathlon\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Triathlon\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Triathlon\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Monitoring group Eau de Paris has tested the river water on a daily basis, yielding results that showed unsafe E. coli levels in recent weeks followed by results in early July that showed improvement.\", \"from\": 837, \"to\": 1037, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 854, \"end\": 866, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Eau_de_Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Eau de Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Eau_de_Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Eau_de_Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Wednesday was a fulfilment of the promise Ms Hidalgo made in January, nine days before the opening ceremony, as part of a broader effort to showcase the river's improved cleanliness.\", \"from\": 1039, \"to\": 1221, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1084, \"end\": 1091, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Miguel_Hidalgo_y_Costilla\", \"score\": 0.9996700753024506, \"rank\": 0.00033003358264419795, \"text\": \"Hidalgo\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Miguel_Hidalgo_y_Costilla\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Miguel_Hidalgo_y_Costilla\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The swim took place along the stretch of the river that passes by the Notre Dame Cathedral and City Hall.\", \"from\": 1223, \"to\": 1328, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Tony Estanguet, head of the Paris 2024 Games, and Marc Guillaume, the prefect of the Paris region, joined Ms Hidalgo.\", \"from\": 1330, \"to\": 1447, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1330, \"end\": 1344, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tony_Estanguet\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Tony Estanguet\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tony_Estanguet\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tony_Estanguet\"}, {\"begin\": 1415, \"end\": 1420, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999969297733, \"rank\": 3.0702673408163037e-09, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wik